WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:09.009
[♪ epic theme music playing]

2
00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:56.241
[sheep bleating]

3
00:02:06.585 --> 00:02:08.003
[bleating]

4
00:02:11.089 --> 00:02:13.133
[dragon grunting]

5
00:02:13.175 --> 00:02:15.177
[bellowing]

6
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:20.974
[chittering]

7
00:02:41.495 --> 00:02:43.121
[dragon grunting]

8
00:02:47.125 --> 00:02:48.293
[gasps]

9
00:02:49.461 --> 00:02:51.338
[speaks High Valyrian]

10
00:03:03.975 --> 00:03:05.977
[dragon snarling]

11
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:10.732
[growling]

12
00:03:17.864 --> 00:03:19.324
[gasps]

13
00:03:20.909 --> 00:03:22.911
[grunting]

14
00:03:25.497 --> 00:03:27.499
[dragon vocalizing]

15
00:03:30.836 --> 00:03:32.504
[grunting]

16
00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:35.382
[shouting]

17
00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:40.512
[grunting]

18
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:46.059
[screaming]

19
00:03:53.567 --> 00:03:55.569
[banging]

20
00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:00.115
[metal clanging]

21
00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:05.036
[grunting]

22
00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:11.668
Kneel.

23
00:04:11.710 --> 00:04:13.670
[sword unsheathing]

24
00:04:13.712 --> 00:04:15.422
[grunting]

25
00:04:15.464 --> 00:04:17.549
I can make it clean. or...

26
00:04:17.591 --> 00:04:19.718
Might I at least know
the accusation. my prince?

27
00:04:19.760 --> 00:04:21.845
Where is he?

28
00:04:21.887 --> 00:04:23.680
- Who?
- My brother. the king.

29
00:04:23.722 --> 00:04:24.931
In his quarters!

30
00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:28.393
You are a traitor
to the crown.

31
00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:30.103
- I sentence you to die.
- No!

32
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:31.813
- [Ironrod] My prince.
- [gasps]

33
00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:35.901
It appears Lord Larys
has fled the Keep as well.

34
00:04:39.237 --> 00:04:40.238
Mm.

35
00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:45.952
[bird squawking]

36
00:04:48.747 --> 00:04:50.874
[groaning]

37
00:04:50.916 --> 00:04:53.084
I need milk of the poppy.

38
00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:56.087
I'm afraid in our hasty flight
that I neglected to bring any.

39
00:04:56.129 --> 00:04:57.881
Ah. the pain!

40
00:04:57.923 --> 00:05:00.258
Please. Please.

41
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:03.261
Take heart. my king.

42
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:05.931
These are dark hours. but...

43
00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:09.059
brighter days lie ahead.

44
00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:11.353
No. No.

45
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:14.773
I'm the king of nothing.

46
00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:20.153
With raven shit for a throne
and a cripple for a protector.

47
00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:23.281
- Oh. I'm fucking pathetic.
- [people shouting]

48
00:05:23.323 --> 00:05:25.242
- [horses whinnying]
- [groaning]

49
00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:27.118
- [shouting continues]
- [thumping]

50
00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:29.538
Oh. fuck!
[groaning]

51
00:05:31.122 --> 00:05:32.582
[shushing]

52
00:05:32.624 --> 00:05:34.084
Draw your hood.

53
00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:36.127
- [birds squawking]
- [shouting continues]

54
00:05:36.962 --> 00:05:38.255
[groaning]

55
00:05:38.296 --> 00:05:39.673
- [shushing]
- [door thumping]

56
00:05:49.307 --> 00:05:51.309
[Man shouting]

57
00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:54.896
Wait. no. wait!
[wincing]

58
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:01.278
Who are you?

59
00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:03.280
Simple men in service
of the Citadel.

60
00:06:03.321 --> 00:06:05.115
[groaning softly]

61
00:06:05.156 --> 00:06:07.200
We're taking these ravens
to White Harbor.

62
00:06:07.242 --> 00:06:09.286
You're in the queen's lands.

63
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:13.456
If you mean to pass. you first
have to denounce the usurper.

64
00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:15.125
bend the knee.

65
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:17.168
You swear fealty
to Her Grace.

66
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:20.964
the one true queen.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

67
00:06:21.006 --> 00:06:23.008
[chuckles]

68
00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:27.554
We denounce the usurper

69
00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:30.682
and swear to Her Grace.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

70
00:06:36.688 --> 00:06:38.899
Come on. friend.
Affirm your fealty

71
00:06:38.940 --> 00:06:40.358
so we might be on our way.

72
00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:42.402
[huffing]

73
00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:46.573
- [groaning lightly]
- The captain said kneel.

74
00:06:46.615 --> 00:06:48.575
Fuck you.
[spitting]

75
00:06:50.577 --> 00:06:52.370
- [grunting]
- [coughing]

76
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:54.497
[soldier chuckles]

77
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.166
Forgive my friend.
he can be so stubborn.

78
00:06:56.207 --> 00:06:58.168
- [continues coughing]
- They're for Aegon.

79
00:06:58.877 --> 00:07:00.712
- Put them to the sword.
- [sword unsheathing]

80
00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:02.881
- Ahh. Wait. please. Please.
- It's a very lucky day
for you. my lord.

81
00:07:05.133 --> 00:07:08.970
The reason this man won't swear
fealty to Rhaenyra...

82
00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:13.725
is because he is
Aegon Targaryen.

83
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:17.562
What?

84
00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:19.898
No. no. that's--

85
00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:22.776
What are you playing at. friend?
Always jesting.

86
00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:24.693
- That true?
- No.

87
00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:27.364
No. of course not.
These-- these are lies.

88
00:07:27.405 --> 00:07:29.741
He was lustrated in dragonfire
by Rhaenys Targaryen...

89
00:07:29.783 --> 00:07:31.868
- No.
- ...and her dragon
at the Battle of Rook's Rest.

90
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:33.702
My companion is always
the gifted mummer.

91
00:07:33.703 --> 00:07:36.081
- I am His Grace's
loyal councillor...
- Always making grand claims

92
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.374
- for his entertainment.
- ...and the Lord of Harrenhal--

93
00:07:37.415 --> 00:07:39.125
Outrageous fucking lies!

94
00:07:39.167 --> 00:07:40.377
Someone's lying.

95
00:07:40.418 --> 00:07:42.087
- His crown.
- No.

96
00:07:46.466 --> 00:07:47.968
[coughing]

97
00:08:01.815 --> 00:08:03.441
Pretty hair.

98
00:08:05.652 --> 00:08:07.028
Take their heads.

99
00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:10.657
- They'll make a rich bounty
for the queen.
- Forgive me. my lord...

100
00:08:10.699 --> 00:08:12.701
- No. no. no. please.
- ...but you would lose your
own head for such a misstep.

101
00:08:14.786 --> 00:08:16.621
This is the challenger himself.

102
00:08:18.707 --> 00:08:20.875
You can name your price
for delivering him...

103
00:08:21.876 --> 00:08:25.422
and his most trusted confidant
to the queen

104
00:08:25.463 --> 00:08:27.340
as living hostages.

105
00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:31.011
Who are they. then?

106
00:08:31.052 --> 00:08:32.721
No one of consequence.

107
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:37.517
- [grunting]
- What's the nearest port?

108
00:08:37.559 --> 00:08:38.810
- Duskendale.
- [sword slicing]

109
00:08:40.145 --> 00:08:41.187
Bar them within.

110
00:08:41.229 --> 00:08:42.522
We'll take them there.

111
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:45.734
And hire a ship
to Dragonstone.

112
00:08:48.653 --> 00:08:50.363
I have to believe...

113
00:08:51.990 --> 00:08:54.159
that Alicent's offer
was genuine.

114
00:08:55.493 --> 00:08:58.872
[Jace]
It is a ruse cloaked
in stale friendship.

115
00:08:58.913 --> 00:09:01.541
The risk she took in coming here
is beyond question.

116
00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:04.502
And the risk
she now asks you to take?

117
00:09:07.505 --> 00:09:12.260
To fly to the Greens' stronghold
based on her word alone.

118
00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:16.514
It is a trap. Mother...

119
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:21.019
to lure you and Daemon
into Vhagar's jaws.

120
00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:23.396
No! Vhagar and Aemond
are gone.

121
00:09:23.438 --> 00:09:25.148
They have flown to Harrenhal.

122
00:09:25.190 --> 00:09:28.693
And Aegon is bedridden.

123
00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:40.330
I could take both Aegon
and the throne

124
00:09:40.371 --> 00:09:42.040
in a single stroke.

125
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:43.083
No.

126
00:09:44.125 --> 00:09:46.086
You cannot trust her.

127
00:09:46.544 --> 00:09:48.213
[footsteps approaching]

128
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:49.631
Mother.

129
00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:54.344
Alicent came to Dragonstone.

130
00:09:54.385 --> 00:09:57.430
- Alicent?
- Under a banner of peace.

131
00:09:57.472 --> 00:09:59.849
- Surely. this is not possible.
- The Greens know already

132
00:09:59.891 --> 00:10:01.434
that their defeat is written.

133
00:10:04.062 --> 00:10:07.107
Aemond flies on Vhagar

134
00:10:07.148 --> 00:10:08.650
to join Cole
in the Riverlands.

135
00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:13.446
With him gone.
Alicent will open the gates
of the Red Keep

136
00:10:13.488 --> 00:10:15.865
and surrender Aegon to me.

137
00:10:15.907 --> 00:10:18.409
I will then take his head
and the throne.

138
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:20.537
What are her terms.
Your Grace?

139
00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:22.956
That she. Helaena.
and Jaehaera are spared.

140
00:10:22.997 --> 00:10:25.583
and that this war ends
without further bloodshed.

141
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:26.960
That is a low price.

142
00:10:27.001 --> 00:10:28.711
Do you believe
she can be trusted?

143
00:10:28.753 --> 00:10:30.797
Uh. get word to Lord Corlys
in the Gullet.

144
00:10:30.839 --> 00:10:32.882
I require ships to deliver
fighting men enough

145
00:10:32.924 --> 00:10:34.759
- to secure the city.
- Your Grace. I protest

146
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.220
- this action with all my po--
- And Daemon must
return with haste.

147
00:10:37.262 --> 00:10:38.680
I'll write to him.

148
00:10:39.806 --> 00:10:42.350
We'll fly to King's Landing
in two days' time...

149
00:10:43.351 --> 00:10:45.228
and take the city.

150
00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:48.273
[♪ dramatic music playing]

151
00:10:55.947 --> 00:10:58.575
Good morrow. ser.
My queen.

152
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.118
The king requires
an audience.

153
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:19.179
Rather to the throne room.
Your Grace.

154
00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:34.652
Aemond.

155
00:11:40.992 --> 00:11:42.452
Why are you here?

156
00:11:42.493 --> 00:11:44.495
[heavy doors closing]

157
00:11:49.834 --> 00:11:51.502
Aegon has abdicated
the throne.

158
00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.215
Abdicated?
W-What do you mean?

159
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:58.551
Fled King's Landing
with that toad Larys.

160
00:11:59.886 --> 00:12:02.513
No. Aegon was... bedridden.

161
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:05.308
Where could he have gone?
Why?

162
00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:07.685
Because he's even more stupid
than he is craven.

163
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:11.147
We must send a search party.
He needs to be found
immediately.

164
00:12:11.189 --> 00:12:13.608
Where were you. Mother?

165
00:12:15.235 --> 00:12:17.528
You've not been seen
in the Keep in days.

166
00:12:25.912 --> 00:12:28.664
I was in the Kingswood.
Aemond.

167
00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.875
I have found myself
of little use here of late.

168
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.589
And what of Harrenhal?

169
00:12:37.632 --> 00:12:39.884
You and Vhagar were meant
to fly to meet Ser Criston

170
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:41.552
and challenge Daemon
together.

171
00:12:43.721 --> 00:12:45.098
Aegon has left me no choice

172
00:12:45.139 --> 00:12:46.891
but to remain here
and defend the city.

173
00:12:49.727 --> 00:12:52.230
But aid is coming.

174
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:54.565
Lord Ormund
and 15.000 Hightower men

175
00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:57.026
presently march up the Mander
with Daeron and his dragon.

176
00:12:57.068 --> 00:12:59.404
And the Triarchy fleet
will. at any moment.

177
00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:02.657
ambush the blockade with a force
thrice the Sea Snake's strength.

178
00:13:07.954 --> 00:13:09.580
We only need to bide our time.

179
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:19.424
[♪ dramatic music playing]

180
00:13:34.772 --> 00:13:36.774
[metal scraping]

181
00:13:40.194 --> 00:13:41.863
[crew member shouting]

182
00:13:48.536 --> 00:13:50.538
♪

183
00:14:06.137 --> 00:14:07.221
- [sword slicing]
- [soldier gagging]

184
00:14:23.988 --> 00:14:25.990
[screaming]

185
00:14:45.551 --> 00:14:47.345
The Lannister host
has scattered. my prince.

186
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:50.390
The vanguard was smashed
and the rearguard
broken and fled.

187
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.270
And what of
the golden Lord Lannister?

188
00:14:57.355 --> 00:14:59.190
Fled when the cavalry
broke rank.

189
00:14:59.232 --> 00:15:01.901
Our scouts believe they may be
regrouping near the God's Eye.

190
00:15:01.943 --> 00:15:03.403
Then we'll continue
the fight there.

191
00:15:03.444 --> 00:15:05.321
We must pursue them
till the last.

192
00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:08.658
- Have graves dug for our dead.
- Aye. my lord.

193
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:11.536
Caraxes would make short work
of these bodies.

194
00:15:11.577 --> 00:15:13.913
And burnt flesh
carries no plague.

195
00:15:13.955 --> 00:15:15.998
[Oscar Tully]
That is not our way.

196
00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:17.959
Rivermen must be returned
to the mud.

197
00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:22.547
My lord!

198
00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:30.638
To arms!

199
00:15:31.556 --> 00:15:32.598
Form on me!

200
00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:34.642
[Caraxes growling]

201
00:15:38.980 --> 00:15:41.983
[chittering]

202
00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:57.081
[♪ tense music playing]

203
00:16:01.586 --> 00:16:04.130
[Caraxes screeching]

204
00:16:26.277 --> 00:16:28.279
♪

205
00:16:43.377 --> 00:16:47.673
We have come to die
for the dragon queen.

206
00:16:57.725 --> 00:17:01.103
Very good.
We've got more lions to hunt.

207
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:02.271
[shouting]

208
00:17:02.313 --> 00:17:04.315
[army shouting]

209
00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:07.902
♪

210
00:17:19.372 --> 00:17:21.374
[people chattering faintly]

211
00:17:25.753 --> 00:17:27.755
[woman sobbing]

212
00:17:37.181 --> 00:17:39.183
[sobbing continues]

213
00:17:55.866 --> 00:17:57.410
Good morrow. Lord Hand.

214
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:02.290
Has there been word
from Prince Aemond?

215
00:18:03.374 --> 00:18:05.459
None. As yet.

216
00:18:07.545 --> 00:18:09.046
He and Vhagar were
supposed to have joined us

217
00:18:09.088 --> 00:18:10.423
back at the Antlers.

218
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:14.510
We march ever exposed.

219
00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:16.387
- If he does not come--
- He has to come.

220
00:18:21.309 --> 00:18:22.727
There is another matter.

221
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.980
One of our men
has ravaged a village girl.

222
00:18:26.981 --> 00:18:28.399
I witnessed the events myself.

223
00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:31.319
Something must be done.

224
00:18:32.570 --> 00:18:34.822
Hang him then. if you wish.

225
00:18:35.906 --> 00:18:38.075
I am not his Lord Commander.

226
00:18:41.245 --> 00:18:43.539
A punishment is due. yes.

227
00:18:43.581 --> 00:18:46.334
but also a statement
to the men.

228
00:18:47.251 --> 00:18:49.754
That we are not beasts.
but knights.

229
00:18:49.795 --> 00:18:51.255
and soldiers of honor.

230
00:18:51.297 --> 00:18:52.923
Look around you.
Ser Gwayne.

231
00:18:56.093 --> 00:18:59.263
Look to the sky.
To the horizon.

232
00:19:00.765 --> 00:19:02.433
Doom and ruin surround us.

233
00:19:05.269 --> 00:19:08.272
We will all become beasts
before our end.

234
00:19:08.314 --> 00:19:10.274
Only if we abandon
our principles.

235
00:19:14.779 --> 00:19:16.781
[dragon chittering]

236
00:19:18.783 --> 00:19:20.451
[Ulf]
Never knew my mother.

237
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:25.539
Same as most of the gutter-rats.

238
00:19:30.169 --> 00:19:32.880
Was kicked about
more than a mongrel dog.

239
00:19:39.136 --> 00:19:41.639
Wished for death more days
than I wished to live.

240
00:19:47.645 --> 00:19:50.398
There was this priest
from Essos.

241
00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:55.820
He fancied me.
Paid me coin.

242
00:20:00.491 --> 00:20:01.575
To do things.

243
00:20:06.497 --> 00:20:08.499
He said I had king's blood.

244
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:11.001
That I was born
for a purpose.

245
00:20:13.546 --> 00:20:14.922
I liked that story.

246
00:20:16.674 --> 00:20:17.883
So I owned it.

247
00:20:20.094 --> 00:20:21.762
Ulf the Dragonseed.

248
00:20:26.934 --> 00:20:28.936
And that red cunt was right.

249
00:20:33.190 --> 00:20:34.567
And you?

250
00:20:34.608 --> 00:20:36.694
Where'd you get
your dragon's blood?

251
00:20:40.698 --> 00:20:43.242
[dragons snarling.
screeching softly]

252
00:20:43.284 --> 00:20:44.535
Did you hear something?

253
00:20:47.872 --> 00:20:49.665
Don't like this place.

254
00:20:49.707 --> 00:20:51.751
All this hanging about.

255
00:20:51.792 --> 00:20:53.586
Vhagar was supposed
to be here already.

256
00:20:53.627 --> 00:20:55.171
We have to wait
until she comes.

257
00:20:55.212 --> 00:20:57.173
The queen didn't say
nothing about waiting.

258
00:20:57.214 --> 00:20:59.507
She said. come here.
kill Aemond.

259
00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:01.594
I wouldn't be too keen
to meet Vhagar.

260
00:21:02.303 --> 00:21:04.597
She and the One-Eye
have slain at least
two dragons already.

261
00:21:04.638 --> 00:21:06.390
Fight'll be worth it. though.

262
00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:08.768
For the castle.

263
00:21:09.894 --> 00:21:11.729
What castle?

264
00:21:11.771 --> 00:21:14.774
The queen promised
to make us knights.

265
00:21:14.815 --> 00:21:16.734
so we get a castle.

266
00:21:24.617 --> 00:21:26.952
- What?
- [Addam] You have
to be named a lord

267
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:28.120
to get a castle.

268
00:21:28.162 --> 00:21:29.789
- What's a knight get. then?
- A horse.

269
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:31.791
What do I need
with a fucking horse?

270
00:21:31.832 --> 00:21:34.542
- I've got a dragon.
- You'd be Ser Ulf.

271
00:21:34.543 --> 00:21:36.378
and men would have
to show you respect.

272
00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:38.464
Men would have
to show me respect

273
00:21:38.506 --> 00:21:40.424
'cause of the big
fucking dragon.

274
00:21:40.466 --> 00:21:42.384
[dragon snarling]

275
00:21:42.426 --> 00:21:43.761
I can't live in a title.

276
00:21:44.637 --> 00:21:45.805
Or drink it.

277
00:21:50.476 --> 00:21:52.269
I imagine there'd be
eager women.

278
00:21:54.438 --> 00:21:56.273
Get more women
with a castle.

279
00:21:58.317 --> 00:22:00.528
- [Sheepstealer growling]
- [Rhaena screaming]

280
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:12.122
[Sheepstealer bellowing]

281
00:22:24.635 --> 00:22:26.637
[singing in High Valyrian]

282
00:22:28.222 --> 00:22:29.597
[roaring]

283
00:22:29.598 --> 00:22:30.641
[gasps]

284
00:22:31.475 --> 00:22:33.644
[speaking High Valyrian]

285
00:22:43.863 --> 00:22:46.532
♪

286
00:22:49.577 --> 00:22:51.412
[screeching]

287
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:57.918
[quill scribbling]

288
00:23:02.172 --> 00:23:04.592
Did you know Aegon had fled?

289
00:23:08.929 --> 00:23:10.097
He was meant to be here.

290
00:23:11.557 --> 00:23:13.517
It's Aemond
who should have flown.

291
00:23:14.852 --> 00:23:16.020
You're frightened.

292
00:23:19.732 --> 00:23:22.192
Ser Criston and Ser Gwayne
are in great peril.

293
00:23:23.277 --> 00:23:24.904
I fear only for our knights.

294
00:23:27.031 --> 00:23:28.324
Aemond should be with them.

295
00:23:28.365 --> 00:23:30.159
Aemond's frightened. too.

296
00:23:30.200 --> 00:23:32.202
[sighs]

297
00:23:32.244 --> 00:23:35.748
After he claimed Vhagar.
he forgot what fear was.

298
00:23:36.874 --> 00:23:38.250
But he remembers now.

299
00:23:39.585 --> 00:23:42.880
He knows that if he has to face
Rhaenyra's dragons. he'll die.

300
00:23:52.264 --> 00:23:53.724
Ser Soren?

301
00:23:58.771 --> 00:24:01.690
Lord Ormund marches here
with the Hightower host.

302
00:24:01.732 --> 00:24:03.192
Dispatch one of
your fastest riders

303
00:24:03.233 --> 00:24:05.069
and deliver this
to him with haste.

304
00:24:05.903 --> 00:24:07.237
These are
the king's instructions.

305
00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:08.405
The king's?

306
00:24:10.324 --> 00:24:12.743
- With haste. Ser Soren.
- At once. Your Grace.

307
00:24:13.786 --> 00:24:14.912
[door closes]

308
00:24:16.288 --> 00:24:17.665
Alyn. sit.

309
00:24:37.267 --> 00:24:38.602
I saved this one.

310
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:42.147
It's from Ib.

311
00:24:43.315 --> 00:24:45.359
Such luxury
is wasted on me.

312
00:24:46.193 --> 00:24:49.113
- [cork popping]
- I've already broken the wax.

313
00:24:52.116 --> 00:24:54.118
And I am not prepared...

314
00:24:57.121 --> 00:24:58.622
to drink alone.

315
00:25:06.338 --> 00:25:07.631
[sighs]

316
00:25:12.052 --> 00:25:13.095
[coughing]

317
00:25:13.137 --> 00:25:15.472
[chuckles]

318
00:25:15.514 --> 00:25:18.475
I forget the guttural name
they have for it.

319
00:25:20.019 --> 00:25:22.855
But I believe
a rough interpretation
is "dragon water."

320
00:25:22.896 --> 00:25:24.314
[clearing throat]

321
00:25:25.399 --> 00:25:27.484
An acquired taste. perhaps.

322
00:25:29.486 --> 00:25:30.821
The queen has sent word.

323
00:25:32.281 --> 00:25:34.116
We are to pull five ships
from the blockade.

324
00:25:34.158 --> 00:25:36.994
sail down the Blackwater.
and seize King's Landing's port.

325
00:25:37.036 --> 00:25:38.829
She's taking King's Landing?

326
00:25:38.871 --> 00:25:40.789
Rhaenyra's advantage
is now absolute.

327
00:25:40.831 --> 00:25:43.709
She will surround the city
with her dragons

328
00:25:43.751 --> 00:25:46.003
and force the surrender
of Aegon and Aemond.

329
00:25:47.337 --> 00:25:49.465
I admit I know little
of this enemy.

330
00:25:50.841 --> 00:25:52.342
But Aemond One-Eye
seems the sort

331
00:25:52.384 --> 00:25:54.845
who would sooner let it all burn
than abandon the throne.

332
00:25:57.264 --> 00:25:58.849
Rough seas lie ahead.

333
00:26:12.362 --> 00:26:15.407
I cannot fully mend...

334
00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:20.871
the... breach between us.

335
00:26:22.372 --> 00:26:24.541
But I do accept
that it was of my making.

336
00:26:29.797 --> 00:26:31.215
I was fond of your mother.

337
00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:34.384
For...

338
00:26:35.469 --> 00:26:36.970
whatever we had together.

339
00:26:39.723 --> 00:26:41.350
[scoffs softly]

340
00:26:41.391 --> 00:26:43.435
I did try to provide
a life for you.

341
00:26:45.104 --> 00:26:48.524
- For your brother.
- A life. perhaps.

342
00:26:48.565 --> 00:26:50.067
But never a name.

343
00:26:58.450 --> 00:27:00.119
I am sorry for it.

344
00:27:01.495 --> 00:27:05.207
- [bell ringing rapidly]
- [crewman] Sail ho!

345
00:27:05.249 --> 00:27:07.334
- [shouting continues]
- [bell continues ringing]

346
00:27:24.143 --> 00:27:26.478
[crewman]
Enemy ships sighted!

347
00:27:28.772 --> 00:27:31.108
[crew member shouting
indistinctly]

348
00:27:33.443 --> 00:27:35.779
- Enemy ships sighted.
- What is their strength?

349
00:27:35.821 --> 00:27:37.406
Three-and-fifty
counted so far.

350
00:27:37.447 --> 00:27:38.615
They already outnumber us.

351
00:27:40.242 --> 00:27:43.412
Put the oars out.
Send ravens to Dragonstone.

352
00:27:43.453 --> 00:27:45.080
[crew member]
Put the oars out!

353
00:27:45.122 --> 00:27:46.582
Take us to the head
of the blockade

354
00:27:46.623 --> 00:27:48.959
and signal the fleet:
form battle lines.

355
00:27:49.001 --> 00:27:50.878
Is it the Lannisters
or the Greyjoys?

356
00:27:51.962 --> 00:27:53.297
It's the Triarchy.

357
00:27:55.799 --> 00:27:57.593
Bring my armor.

358
00:27:57.634 --> 00:28:00.637
[♪ dramatic music playing]

359
00:28:17.821 --> 00:28:20.157
[crew members chattering]

360
00:28:20.199 --> 00:28:21.325
[Tyland Lannister]
Commander.

361
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:25.954
The Gullet has three inlets
into the Blackwater.

362
00:28:25.996 --> 00:28:29.833
the largest of which opens
just to the south of Driftmark.

363
00:28:29.875 --> 00:28:31.627
But I hold strongly
that we must press

364
00:28:31.668 --> 00:28:33.295
towards the southern inlet.

365
00:28:33.337 --> 00:28:36.840
If our armada engages
the Velaryon fleet
at close combat.

366
00:28:36.882 --> 00:28:39.009
it will blunt the threat
of Rhaenyra's dragons.

367
00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:41.386
They will be loath
to burn their own ships.

368
00:28:41.428 --> 00:28:43.013
A canny strategy. my lord.

369
00:28:44.056 --> 00:28:46.683
I can see why your king
made you Lord of the Ships.

370
00:28:46.725 --> 00:28:48.018
[crunching]

371
00:28:49.770 --> 00:28:52.481
You'll rule all this kit
if you wind up in the drink.

372
00:28:52.522 --> 00:28:54.316
[chuckles]

373
00:28:54.358 --> 00:28:57.736
My strategy is expressly
not to "end up in the drink."

374
00:29:00.489 --> 00:29:03.492
We will face death on this deck
before we face it in the sea.

375
00:29:04.284 --> 00:29:06.536
You will be glad of our armor
when the fighting starts.

376
00:29:06.578 --> 00:29:08.080
I know I will.

377
00:29:08.121 --> 00:29:11.208
The Sea Snake scouts have
raised the alarm. Commander.

378
00:29:12.417 --> 00:29:14.378
If only to see his face.

379
00:29:15.712 --> 00:29:17.673
Signal Halfjaw
to take his detachment

380
00:29:17.714 --> 00:29:19.341
and penetrate
the northern pass.

381
00:29:19.383 --> 00:29:21.009
- Mm.
- [Tyland] The northern pass

382
00:29:21.051 --> 00:29:22.344
is the farthest route

383
00:29:22.386 --> 00:29:24.096
running north of Dragonstone.
Whatever for?

384
00:29:25.097 --> 00:29:26.431
To sack High Tide.

385
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:29.226
Lord Corlys' castle?

386
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:32.854
We will require
the full strength of your fleet

387
00:29:32.896 --> 00:29:34.731
- if we have any hope--
- High Tide is a monument

388
00:29:34.773 --> 00:29:36.275
to the Sea Snake himself.

389
00:29:38.735 --> 00:29:40.195
Do you think
his focus will hold

390
00:29:40.237 --> 00:29:42.322
when he sees
his treasure room aflame?

391
00:29:46.118 --> 00:29:47.119
Uh...

392
00:29:48.120 --> 00:29:50.371
[wind whistling]

393
00:29:50.372 --> 00:29:52.416
[Sheepstealer vocalizing]

394
00:29:57.296 --> 00:29:59.798
[Sheepstealer snarling softly]

395
00:29:59.840 --> 00:30:01.842
[growling softly]

396
00:30:04.094 --> 00:30:06.096
[retching]

397
00:30:20.610 --> 00:30:22.779
[vocalizing]

398
00:30:44.676 --> 00:30:46.678
[people chattering]

399
00:30:54.394 --> 00:30:55.645
[Tessarion calling]

400
00:31:05.364 --> 00:31:08.033
What is the weather
to be today. Bold Jon?

401
00:31:08.075 --> 00:31:10.535
Raining piss or shit.
from the looks of the messenger.

402
00:31:11.745 --> 00:31:13.038
[horse whinnying]

403
00:31:13.080 --> 00:31:16.291
Good morrow. ser.
What news?

404
00:31:16.333 --> 00:31:18.001
Good morrow.
my Lord Hightower.

405
00:31:20.379 --> 00:31:22.005
I bring urgent word
from King Aemond.

406
00:31:22.839 --> 00:31:24.174
King. is he now?

407
00:31:25.217 --> 00:31:26.802
[insect buzzing]

408
00:31:26.843 --> 00:31:28.845
[sniffing. groaning]

409
00:31:30.722 --> 00:31:32.224
[clearing throat]

410
00:31:32.265 --> 00:31:33.433
[sniffing]

411
00:31:55.038 --> 00:31:56.832
Aemond says we have
to make camp here

412
00:31:56.873 --> 00:31:58.375
and await further word.

413
00:31:59.292 --> 00:32:01.128
He shall join us
in three days' time.

414
00:32:07.634 --> 00:32:09.219
So Aegon's dead. then?

415
00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:15.642
One king is as good as another.

416
00:32:16.476 --> 00:32:18.979
[clearing throat]
Have this lad bathed and fed.

417
00:32:19.020 --> 00:32:20.897
- Give him a good tent.
- Yes. sire.

418
00:32:25.402 --> 00:32:27.904
Mayhaps the weather will hold.

419
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:36.121
[Alicent] <i>It is my fault
we're in this position.</i>

420
00:32:46.840 --> 00:32:50.093
I strove tirelessly to put Aegon
on the throne. but I...

421
00:32:52.345 --> 00:32:54.264
I failed to prepare him
to rule.

422
00:32:58.977 --> 00:33:00.937
His frailties are his own.

423
00:33:06.818 --> 00:33:08.487
You should have been king.

424
00:33:12.616 --> 00:33:14.618
If you'd only been born first.
then perhaps

425
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:16.536
we wouldn't be here. but...

426
00:33:18.497 --> 00:33:20.624
we must ever play
the board before us.

427
00:33:31.051 --> 00:33:35.639
That is why you need
to go to Harrenhal.

428
00:33:40.685 --> 00:33:41.811
To what end?

429
00:33:41.853 --> 00:33:43.647
It is a stronghold.

430
00:33:44.898 --> 00:33:47.608
One that has withstood
dragonfire once before.

431
00:33:47.609 --> 00:33:50.362
You are no longer safe here
in King's Landing.

432
00:33:58.495 --> 00:34:00.872
It is well to be fearful.

433
00:34:00.914 --> 00:34:02.415
I. too. am afraid.

434
00:34:05.752 --> 00:34:07.379
I'm not afraid.

435
00:34:10.674 --> 00:34:11.925
[Alicent sighs]

436
00:34:14.844 --> 00:34:16.012
Of course not.

437
00:34:16.846 --> 00:34:18.223
But you are the crown now.

438
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:22.686
[sighs] And Rhaenyra will send
her new dragons here for you.

439
00:34:23.853 --> 00:34:25.021
Soon or late.

440
00:34:28.608 --> 00:34:30.235
I am not afraid.

441
00:34:36.032 --> 00:34:37.492
Fly to the Riverlands.

442
00:34:37.534 --> 00:34:39.202
Draw Daemon out.

443
00:34:40.203 --> 00:34:41.663
He has just one dragon.
and killing him

444
00:34:41.705 --> 00:34:43.540
would be a vicious blow
to Rhaenyra.

445
00:34:45.709 --> 00:34:48.712
At Harrenhal.
you will be unassailable.

446
00:34:53.049 --> 00:34:54.593
Perhaps I could
even meet you there.

447
00:34:57.721 --> 00:34:59.264
That road is uncertain.

448
00:35:01.224 --> 00:35:02.767
But this one.

449
00:35:02.809 --> 00:35:04.853
if you stay here
and wait for Rhaenyra

450
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:08.189
and her dragons to come.
this one is certain.

451
00:35:08.231 --> 00:35:09.232
[sighs]

452
00:35:12.819 --> 00:35:14.404
You are so courageous.

453
00:35:16.865 --> 00:35:18.908
But I cannot lose you
as I did Aegon.

454
00:35:21.411 --> 00:35:23.079
If I do. I will be lost.

455
00:35:26.291 --> 00:35:28.627
Heed me. Aemond. please.

456
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:09.542
I shall host a feast there
in your honor.

457
00:36:10.794 --> 00:36:12.379
In Black Harren's hall

458
00:36:13.880 --> 00:36:16.174
whilst my uncle's head
looks down from a spike.

459
00:36:22.972 --> 00:36:24.724
[door opens]

460
00:36:26.976 --> 00:36:27.977
[door closes]

461
00:36:29.729 --> 00:36:31.481
[farting and grunting]

462
00:36:32.982 --> 00:36:34.776
[flatulence continues]

463
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:36.152
- [leaves rustling]
- [gasps]

464
00:36:41.991 --> 00:36:42.992
[gasps]

465
00:36:43.702 --> 00:36:45.412
- [growling]
- Fuck!

466
00:36:47.580 --> 00:36:51.292
What if Aemond
knew we were coming for him?

467
00:36:51.334 --> 00:36:53.420
He could have attacked
Dragonstone in our absence.

468
00:36:54.546 --> 00:36:57.674
Queen assigned us a task.
We must man steadfastly.

469
00:36:58.842 --> 00:37:01.136
And if that is what the enemy
is counting upon?

470
00:37:05.432 --> 00:37:07.434
[snarling]

471
00:37:11.896 --> 00:37:13.815
- What is that?
- [Ulf] Fuck this place!

472
00:37:13.857 --> 00:37:16.568
- What's happened?
- I'm leaving
is what's happened.

473
00:37:16.609 --> 00:37:18.153
We must wait for Vhagar.

474
00:37:18.194 --> 00:37:20.822
For how long?
Forever and a day?

475
00:37:20.864 --> 00:37:22.365
She was meant
to be here already.

476
00:37:24.367 --> 00:37:26.326
The queen only instructed us
to ambush Vhagar.

477
00:37:26.327 --> 00:37:28.037
She did not say what to do
if the dragon never came.

478
00:37:28.079 --> 00:37:29.664
I say we remain.

479
00:37:29.706 --> 00:37:31.249
Who made you fucking king?

480
00:37:31.291 --> 00:37:32.876
- [snarling]
- I don't like it here.

481
00:37:32.917 --> 00:37:34.544
Is that what you'll tell
Her Grace?

482
00:37:34.586 --> 00:37:37.338
- That you're craven?
- I'll tell Her Grace true.

483
00:37:37.380 --> 00:37:40.675
That we stood watch
and Vhagar never came.

484
00:37:40.717 --> 00:37:42.552
[Alys]
Your friend's right.

485
00:37:46.848 --> 00:37:48.683
You're missing the battle.

486
00:37:48.725 --> 00:37:50.560
The queen needs you
at Dragonstone.

487
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:54.481
Who are you?

488
00:37:55.482 --> 00:37:56.649
I'm a witch.

489
00:38:01.821 --> 00:38:03.531
Right.
Look after yourselves.

490
00:38:03.573 --> 00:38:05.575
[dragon screeching]

491
00:38:16.461 --> 00:38:19.547
[indistinct chatter]

492
00:38:19.589 --> 00:38:20.965
Your Grace!

493
00:38:21.424 --> 00:38:24.302
- There is war in the Gullet.
- Who?

494
00:38:24.344 --> 00:38:25.595
An armada of ships

495
00:38:25.637 --> 00:38:27.722
sailing out of the rising sun
from the east.

496
00:38:27.764 --> 00:38:29.307
They have sprung their trap.

497
00:38:34.938 --> 00:38:36.022
I shall go.

498
00:38:44.113 --> 00:38:45.907
Mother!

499
00:38:45.949 --> 00:38:47.659
Stop!
You cannot!

500
00:38:47.700 --> 00:38:50.411
There is nothing you can say
that I have not heard.

501
00:38:50.453 --> 00:38:51.496
If you die...

502
00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:53.957
Then you will at last be king.

503
00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:56.292
[shouting]

504
00:38:56.334 --> 00:38:57.961
My riding leathers.

505
00:39:06.302 --> 00:39:08.805
You are to lock
and bar this door.

506
00:39:09.722 --> 00:39:12.517
The queen must be confined
until she regains her senses.

507
00:39:12.559 --> 00:39:14.602
I could not defy
Her Grace's commands.

508
00:39:14.644 --> 00:39:18.022
You are a knight of
the Queensguard.
Ser Lorent.

509
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:22.151
You swore to protect
Her Grace from all threats.

510
00:39:23.528 --> 00:39:25.071
Including herself.

511
00:39:30.827 --> 00:39:31.995
Your life...

512
00:39:33.246 --> 00:39:34.414
for hers.

513
00:39:43.256 --> 00:39:44.716
[Baela] Jace.

514
00:39:44.757 --> 00:39:46.175
Rescind your command.

515
00:39:46.217 --> 00:39:48.511
- It is treason.
- She has rejected my counsel.

516
00:39:48.553 --> 00:39:50.054
my every attempt
to join the fight.

517
00:39:50.096 --> 00:39:52.473
So you make war
with her instead?

518
00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:54.976
This is all the work
of an ambush.
like Rook's Rest.

519
00:39:55.018 --> 00:39:57.228
a ruse to draw out
the queen herself.

520
00:39:57.270 --> 00:40:00.189
They killed my brother.
Baela.

521
00:40:01.190 --> 00:40:02.775
I won't let them
take her as well.

522
00:40:10.450 --> 00:40:11.910
Come with me.

523
00:40:13.703 --> 00:40:15.538
We are ready.

524
00:40:17.123 --> 00:40:18.708
We can win
this victory for her.

525
00:40:20.251 --> 00:40:22.754
Was this not always
our purpose?

526
00:40:25.715 --> 00:40:28.635
[♪ dramatic music playing]

527
00:40:42.482 --> 00:40:44.442
[door thuds]

528
00:40:44.484 --> 00:40:46.069
[door rattling]

529
00:40:47.612 --> 00:40:49.948
Ser Lorent. open the door.

530
00:40:49.989 --> 00:40:52.575
Your Grace. it was the
Prince Jacaerys' command.

531
00:40:53.743 --> 00:40:55.078
To ensure your safety.

532
00:40:55.119 --> 00:40:57.205
Open the fucking door.

533
00:40:57.246 --> 00:40:59.290
- I cannot.
- [door thuds]

534
00:40:59.332 --> 00:41:00.917
Ser Lorent!

535
00:41:02.585 --> 00:41:04.087
Jace!

536
00:41:07.006 --> 00:41:08.800
You open the fucking door!

537
00:41:09.634 --> 00:41:12.136
- [banging]
- You release me at once!

538
00:41:12.178 --> 00:41:14.430
[echoing] I will have
your heads for this!

539
00:41:14.472 --> 00:41:16.474
[banging]

540
00:41:20.436 --> 00:41:22.438
[people screaming and shouting]

541
00:41:35.326 --> 00:41:37.328
[screaming continues]

542
00:41:42.959 --> 00:41:45.420
[Alyn]
Crossbows. ready!

543
00:41:45.461 --> 00:41:46.921
Release!

544
00:41:46.963 --> 00:41:49.424
Archers. ready!

545
00:41:49.465 --> 00:41:50.758
- [crew shouting]
- Release!

546
00:41:50.800 --> 00:41:52.260
[bows thwacking]

547
00:41:52.301 --> 00:41:54.470
Archers. ready!

548
00:41:54.512 --> 00:41:56.014
Release!

549
00:41:56.055 --> 00:41:58.516
Barrelman! Signal the fleet:

550
00:41:58.558 --> 00:42:00.268
Do not cluster.

551
00:42:00.309 --> 00:42:01.602
Keep them on the chase.

552
00:42:01.644 --> 00:42:03.604
- [barrelman] Aye-aye!
- The fight is yours.

553
00:42:03.646 --> 00:42:05.189
Archers. ready!

554
00:42:05.231 --> 00:42:07.275
Archers. go!

555
00:42:07.316 --> 00:42:08.317
Loose!

556
00:42:08.359 --> 00:42:10.028
Flagship's been sighted.
m'lord.

557
00:42:11.070 --> 00:42:12.280
It's the <i>Bitchfist.</i>

558
00:42:12.321 --> 00:42:13.322
Lohar?

559
00:42:16.659 --> 00:42:18.953
Harden up
and make towards her.

560
00:42:18.995 --> 00:42:21.372
- I want her to sight us.
- Aye. m'lord.

561
00:42:22.331 --> 00:42:24.208
Harden up!
Pick up the stroke!

562
00:42:29.881 --> 00:42:32.008
[crew shouting]

563
00:42:51.360 --> 00:42:52.820
Here she comes. lads!

564
00:42:52.862 --> 00:42:55.073
Our jewel in the rough.

565
00:42:55.114 --> 00:42:59.077
Signal the fleet.
The Sea Snake belongs to us.

566
00:42:59.118 --> 00:43:02.163
An equal share of the plunder
when we take the ship!

567
00:43:02.205 --> 00:43:03.748
- Aye. Commander!
- Commander!

568
00:43:04.916 --> 00:43:06.501
Commander!

569
00:43:06.542 --> 00:43:08.252
Ours is the flagship.

570
00:43:08.294 --> 00:43:10.588
We cannot give ourselves
to a singular pursuit.

571
00:43:10.630 --> 00:43:13.132
We must lead the assault
lest it fall into disorder.

572
00:43:14.550 --> 00:43:16.344
Do you think I sailed
across the Narrow Sea

573
00:43:16.385 --> 00:43:18.262
to win your king's war for him?

574
00:43:19.889 --> 00:43:22.225
Those were the terms
of the contract.

575
00:43:23.434 --> 00:43:25.645
The Sea Snake led
the persecution and slaughter

576
00:43:25.686 --> 00:43:27.730
of my mates
for more than 20 years.

577
00:43:29.065 --> 00:43:30.650
I sealed your contract for him.

578
00:43:32.401 --> 00:43:36.072
Tonight. we shall walk
in the ashes of High Tide!

579
00:43:36.114 --> 00:43:39.242
You'll all join me as I sit
the Driftwood Throne

580
00:43:39.283 --> 00:43:41.410
and dine on
the Sea Snake's ears!

581
00:43:41.452 --> 00:43:43.955
[crew cheering]

582
00:43:43.996 --> 00:43:45.206
Break us free!

583
00:43:45.248 --> 00:43:46.916
[crew shouting]

584
00:43:46.958 --> 00:43:48.292
[Lohar]
And give chase!

585
00:44:02.932 --> 00:44:04.934
He wishes only
to protect you.

586
00:44:04.976 --> 00:44:06.769
I never asked
to be protected.

587
00:44:18.447 --> 00:44:20.240
I expect it from my council.

588
00:44:20.241 --> 00:44:23.578
those craven men ever clutching
at their doublets.

589
00:44:23.619 --> 00:44:24.996
But my Queensguard?

590
00:44:25.037 --> 00:44:26.497
Mine own son?

591
00:45:19.842 --> 00:45:22.178
I may appear to have the weak
and feeble body of a woman.

592
00:45:22.220 --> 00:45:24.513
but I possess the heart
and spirit of a king.

593
00:45:28.267 --> 00:45:30.311
Enemy to starboard!

594
00:45:30.353 --> 00:45:32.313
- [Alyn] Split. split. split!
- Ballistae. reload!

595
00:45:32.355 --> 00:45:33.856
And put those fires out!

596
00:45:36.359 --> 00:45:37.985
The fleet is surrounded.

597
00:45:38.027 --> 00:45:40.320
And the <i>Bitchfist</i>
now pursues us
with a small detachment.

598
00:45:40.321 --> 00:45:42.698
- [crew members] Dragon!
- [barrelman] Dragon!

599
00:45:42.740 --> 00:45:44.200
[dragon screeching]

600
00:45:45.785 --> 00:45:47.745
[bellowing]

601
00:45:50.539 --> 00:45:52.583
[Jace] <i>Dracarys!</i>

602
00:45:54.710 --> 00:45:56.170
[dragon screeching]

603
00:45:56.212 --> 00:45:57.421
[Baela] <i>Dracarys!</i>

604
00:46:00.549 --> 00:46:02.551
[all cheering]

605
00:46:04.804 --> 00:46:06.806
[dragon calling]

606
00:46:13.729 --> 00:46:15.898
Set a course through
the Dragonstone Pass.

607
00:46:17.900 --> 00:46:20.152
The tide is nearly out.
We'll run aground.

608
00:46:21.570 --> 00:46:24.573
Lohar only wants me.
She'll follow.

609
00:46:25.658 --> 00:46:27.910
Without her. their fleet
will be rudderless...

610
00:46:28.995 --> 00:46:30.746
and easy prey
for our dragons.

611
00:46:33.124 --> 00:46:35.876
- [dragon screeching]
- [crew shouting]

612
00:46:35.918 --> 00:46:37.712
Make ready. men!

613
00:46:37.753 --> 00:46:39.714
Bring the grapnels!

614
00:46:39.755 --> 00:46:41.424
[crew shouting]

615
00:46:46.679 --> 00:46:48.264
- Ready?
- Ready!

616
00:46:51.100 --> 00:46:53.227
[crew members shouting]

617
00:46:53.269 --> 00:46:54.353
Load!

618
00:47:03.612 --> 00:47:05.614
[dragon bellowing]

619
00:47:12.121 --> 00:47:13.122
[grunting]

620
00:47:15.291 --> 00:47:17.626
[Jace grunting.
Vermax screeching]

621
00:47:19.003 --> 00:47:21.213
[speaking High Valyrian]

622
00:47:23.883 --> 00:47:25.301
[cheering]

623
00:47:25.343 --> 00:47:28.304
Call me Lohar. Dragon-Slayer!

624
00:47:28.971 --> 00:47:30.473
Press the pursuit!

625
00:47:35.519 --> 00:47:36.771
[grunting]

626
00:47:36.812 --> 00:47:38.814
[crew shouting]

627
00:47:47.323 --> 00:47:49.283
[Baela speaking High Valyrian]

628
00:47:49.325 --> 00:47:50.993
[Moondancer calling]

629
00:48:00.669 --> 00:48:01.879
[Jace grunting]

630
00:48:05.883 --> 00:48:07.343
[screeching]

631
00:48:24.777 --> 00:48:26.779
[sea birds calling]

632
00:48:33.536 --> 00:48:36.080
Ease the sheets
and put out the oars.

633
00:48:36.122 --> 00:48:38.082
Cast the leadlines.

634
00:48:38.124 --> 00:48:40.084
[Alyn]
Clew up the course.

635
00:48:40.126 --> 00:48:42.420
Leadsmen. to the channels.

636
00:48:42.461 --> 00:48:44.046
Cast the leadline!

637
00:48:46.632 --> 00:48:48.634
[crew member
shouting orders]

638
00:48:50.761 --> 00:48:52.763
[shouting continues]

639
00:48:57.893 --> 00:49:00.563
Depth. six fathoms!

640
00:49:00.604 --> 00:49:02.356
Barrelman. report!

641
00:49:02.398 --> 00:49:05.025
Breakers dead ahead.

642
00:49:05.067 --> 00:49:07.027
Tide's running hard out.

643
00:49:07.069 --> 00:49:09.447
Currents are strong
set to larboard.

644
00:49:14.076 --> 00:49:17.830
Three enemy ships
closing fast astern!

645
00:49:18.664 --> 00:49:19.957
Larboard your helm.

646
00:49:21.792 --> 00:49:23.252
Follow my direction closely.

647
00:49:23.294 --> 00:49:26.130
There is a way through the pass.
but it is narrow.

648
00:49:27.256 --> 00:49:30.301
[Alyn]
Depth: half-five
and fast receding!

649
00:49:32.595 --> 00:49:34.722
- Seven!
- Speed: seven knots!

650
00:49:34.763 --> 00:49:36.557
Slight to larboard.

651
00:49:36.599 --> 00:49:38.058
Aye. Lord Admiral.

652
00:49:38.934 --> 00:49:42.062
- [Lohar] Follow her wake.
- We must go no further.

653
00:49:42.104 --> 00:49:43.898
The pass is too shallow.

654
00:49:43.939 --> 00:49:45.399
[wood thudding]

655
00:49:45.441 --> 00:49:47.443
We do not know
the lay of this place.

656
00:49:48.777 --> 00:49:51.280
- We are sailing blind.
- The Sea Snake will guide us.

657
00:49:58.120 --> 00:50:00.915
- One over four!
- One over four!

658
00:50:00.956 --> 00:50:03.751
Perhaps
70 yards' distance.

659
00:50:03.792 --> 00:50:04.710
Easy now.

660
00:50:05.461 --> 00:50:06.837
Starboard your helm.

661
00:50:09.298 --> 00:50:11.425
- [thud]
- Too strong.

662
00:50:11.467 --> 00:50:12.635
Ease it back.

663
00:50:16.138 --> 00:50:18.307
[crew members shouting]

664
00:50:19.808 --> 00:50:20.893
Let me.

665
00:50:22.728 --> 00:50:24.313
Forty yards now.

666
00:50:25.523 --> 00:50:26.649
Thirty-five!

667
00:50:27.691 --> 00:50:30.486
- And a half-three!
- And a half-three!

668
00:50:30.528 --> 00:50:32.321
Bank the oars.

669
00:50:32.363 --> 00:50:34.782
[Alyn]
Coxswain ahoy!
Bank oars!

670
00:50:34.823 --> 00:50:37.660
[shouting commands]

671
00:50:40.829 --> 00:50:44.291
- Twenty-five yards!
- Twenty-five yards!

672
00:50:44.333 --> 00:50:46.544
- One over three!
- Ten yards!

673
00:50:46.585 --> 00:50:49.004
- Ten yards!
- We're over the Teeth!

674
00:50:49.046 --> 00:50:51.340
[wood creaking]

675
00:50:54.760 --> 00:50:56.762
[loud banging]

676
00:50:58.013 --> 00:50:59.848
[wood creaking]

677
00:51:11.235 --> 00:51:12.570
We're clear!

678
00:51:12.611 --> 00:51:14.613
[crew cheering]

679
00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:23.414
Leave Lohar to the Teeth.

680
00:51:23.455 --> 00:51:26.375
Take us back to the Gullet.
We must rejoin the fight.

681
00:51:27.293 --> 00:51:30.296
[♪ epic music playing]

682
00:51:47.938 --> 00:51:49.315
[speaking High Valyrian]

683
00:51:50.816 --> 00:51:52.818
[Sheepstealer bellowing]

684
00:52:04.079 --> 00:52:06.248
Three hands to starboard.
now!

685
00:52:06.290 --> 00:52:09.084
- Three hands to starboard!
- We're going to wreck!

686
00:52:09.126 --> 00:52:11.128
[loud banging]

687
00:52:16.258 --> 00:52:19.553
We have walked directly
into his snare.

688
00:52:19.595 --> 00:52:21.889
Two hands to larboard now
and hold her there!

689
00:52:21.930 --> 00:52:24.558
- Two hands to larboard. hold!
- Cut the anchors!

690
00:52:24.600 --> 00:52:27.227
Drop weight
and raise our draft.
Quickly!

691
00:52:27.269 --> 00:52:29.605
Aye. Commander!
Cut the anchors!

692
00:52:34.902 --> 00:52:36.612
What do you weigh
in that armor?

693
00:52:37.988 --> 00:52:39.281
[shouting]

694
00:52:40.449 --> 00:52:42.159
And the rest of them!

695
00:52:42.201 --> 00:52:45.746
Hold that line.
and pull the fucking oars in!

696
00:52:45.788 --> 00:52:46.789
[shouting]

697
00:52:49.291 --> 00:52:51.293
[rumbling]

698
00:52:55.964 --> 00:52:57.966
[rumbling stops]

699
00:53:04.056 --> 00:53:05.808
Oars out
and close the distance!

700
00:53:05.849 --> 00:53:07.351
Bring the hooks and lines!

701
00:53:07.393 --> 00:53:10.104
Enemy flagship is clear.

702
00:53:10.145 --> 00:53:12.147
She's closing fast astern.

703
00:53:13.315 --> 00:53:15.776
She has the legs on us.
We can't outrun her.

704
00:53:15.818 --> 00:53:18.028
And we've not yet the wind
to carry us against the current.

705
00:53:19.488 --> 00:53:21.615
Furl the sails
and put the oars out.

706
00:53:21.657 --> 00:53:23.117
Hard round to starboard.

707
00:53:23.158 --> 00:53:25.327
Ready the offensive
for a broadside assault.

708
00:53:25.369 --> 00:53:28.122
All shields and crossbows.
to your stations!

709
00:53:28.163 --> 00:53:29.832
Load the ballistae!

710
00:53:38.757 --> 00:53:41.677
- Boarding party!
- Boarding party.

711
00:53:44.930 --> 00:53:48.517
Hard about and keep pulling!
Strong against the current.

712
00:53:48.559 --> 00:53:50.686
- Turn!
- Or she'll be dragged
back into the Teeth.

713
00:54:05.200 --> 00:54:06.744
She's not turning!

714
00:54:11.081 --> 00:54:12.958
All shields and crossbows
to starboard!

715
00:54:14.626 --> 00:54:16.211
Broadside. ready!

716
00:54:17.755 --> 00:54:19.757
[crew members shouting]

717
00:54:19.798 --> 00:54:22.551
[Alyn]
Positions. move!
Positions!

718
00:54:31.477 --> 00:54:34.021
- Crossbows. ready!
- Ready!

719
00:54:34.062 --> 00:54:35.063
Strike!

720
00:54:39.067 --> 00:54:42.112
Hold that course
and fucking row!

721
00:54:42.780 --> 00:54:43.906
[screaming]

722
00:54:45.073 --> 00:54:47.409
Brace and be ready!

723
00:54:47.451 --> 00:54:48.786
Now. strike!

724
00:54:48.827 --> 00:54:50.579
[loud crashing]

725
00:54:58.128 --> 00:55:00.130
[shouting and screaming]

726
00:55:02.049 --> 00:55:03.425
Take the ship.

727
00:55:03.467 --> 00:55:05.469
[crew shouting]

728
00:55:06.428 --> 00:55:08.972
On your feet!
Prepare to engage!

729
00:55:15.270 --> 00:55:17.272
[shouting]

730
00:55:20.609 --> 00:55:23.612
[♪ dramatic music playing]

731
00:55:27.115 --> 00:55:29.117
[Sheepstealer bellowing]

732
00:55:30.327 --> 00:55:31.829
<i>Dracarys!</i>

733
00:55:32.871 --> 00:55:34.873
[soldiers screaming]

734
00:55:40.546 --> 00:55:42.214
[crew member]
Bring down the rider!

735
00:55:54.226 --> 00:55:55.811
[Soldiers screaming]

736
00:56:00.732 --> 00:56:03.151
[screeching]

737
00:56:11.577 --> 00:56:13.579
[audio muffled]

738
00:56:15.163 --> 00:56:16.498
[grunting]

739
00:56:34.016 --> 00:56:36.018
- [audio clears]
- [overlapping shouting]

740
00:56:55.078 --> 00:56:56.788
[yardarm snapping]

741
00:57:07.925 --> 00:57:09.051
[gasping]

742
00:57:19.978 --> 00:57:21.605
[bellowing]

743
00:57:25.233 --> 00:57:26.568
[screaming]

744
00:57:31.782 --> 00:57:34.076
[grunting. gasping]

745
00:57:39.581 --> 00:57:41.083
[screaming]

746
00:57:47.255 --> 00:57:49.424
[Sheepstealer roaring]

747
00:57:50.842 --> 00:57:52.844
[soldiers screaming]

748
00:58:06.233 --> 00:58:08.276
[dragons bellowing.
screeching]

749
00:58:10.487 --> 00:58:12.489
[speaking High Valyrian]

750
00:58:19.788 --> 00:58:22.082
No! No!

751
00:58:22.124 --> 00:58:24.126
Sheepstealer. no!

752
00:58:27.170 --> 00:58:29.965
- [dragon calling]
- That's my sister.

753
00:59:06.376 --> 00:59:08.378
[ships crashing]

754
00:59:25.854 --> 00:59:27.689
- [shouting]
- [Lohar screaming]

755
00:59:37.908 --> 00:59:39.576
[loud creaking]

756
00:59:47.959 --> 00:59:49.044
Father!

757
00:59:55.217 --> 00:59:56.218
[grunting]

758
01:00:04.643 --> 01:00:06.561
- [bellowing]
- Hold on. Baela!

759
01:00:08.730 --> 01:00:10.065
[screeching]

760
01:00:13.443 --> 01:00:14.569
Rhaena!

761
01:00:19.074 --> 01:00:20.575
[panicked shouting]

762
01:00:22.911 --> 01:00:25.247
[Rhaena]
Sheepstealer!

763
01:00:28.166 --> 01:00:30.585
[dragons continue
bellowing]

764
01:00:32.587 --> 01:00:34.172
[grunting]

765
01:00:35.257 --> 01:00:37.259
[roaring]

766
01:00:38.343 --> 01:00:40.762
[Rhaena]
Sheepstealer! No!

767
01:00:42.973 --> 01:00:45.016
- [thwacking]
- [dragon screeching]

768
01:00:46.143 --> 01:00:47.144
[Jace] Vermax!

769
01:00:49.604 --> 01:00:51.606
[screeching continues]

770
01:01:00.532 --> 01:01:01.825
Jace!

771
01:01:17.299 --> 01:01:19.301
[screeching. roaring]

772
01:01:21.386 --> 01:01:23.388
[both grunting]

773
01:01:28.143 --> 01:01:29.978
[shouting]

774
01:01:31.855 --> 01:01:33.648
[muffled grunting]

775
01:01:36.484 --> 01:01:37.569
[shouting]

776
01:01:41.990 --> 01:01:43.325
[muffled grunting]

777
01:01:44.034 --> 01:01:45.202
[knife unsheathing]

778
01:01:45.243 --> 01:01:46.870
- [gasps]
- [growling]

779
01:01:49.497 --> 01:01:52.167
[exclaiming]

780
01:01:59.049 --> 01:02:01.051
[breathing heavily]

781
01:02:04.846 --> 01:02:06.848
[screeching]

782
01:02:07.724 --> 01:02:09.559
Jace!

783
